dct_title_s: Greece and the Aegean : atlas plate 40 : December 1958 / compiled and drawn in the Cartographic Division of the National Geographic Society for the National Geographic Magazine.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by shading and spot heights. Depth shown by bathymetric tints and soundings. Includes insets: "The Bosporus", "The Dardanelles," and [Athens Region]. Shows roads, railroads, airports, oil fields, oil pipe lines, ruins, battle sites, drainage, countries, and cities.
dct_publisher_sm: Baltimore, M.D. : A. Hoen and Co., 1958.
